## MobSF (Mobile Security Framework)

What it is: An automated, all-in-one mobile application pentesting framework that performs static and dynamic analysis.

## Key Features
  -Automated static analysis with comprehensive reports
  -API scanning for backend services
  -Dynamic analysis with emulator/real device support
  -Generates HTML, PDF, and JSON reports
  -Scans for known vulnerabilities in third-party libraries

## Primary Use

# Docker setup (recommended)
docker run -it -p 8000:8000 opensecurity/mobile-security-framework-mobsf

# Then open http://localhost:8000 and upload your APK

## What You Can Find
  -Manifest issues: Dangerous permissions, exported components
  -Code vulnerabilities: Hardcoded secrets, insecure cryptography
  -Binary analysis: Third-party libraries with CVEs
  -Network security: HTTP traffic, SSL bypass
  -Data storage: Insecure file permissions, SQL injection

## Advantages Over Other Tools
  -Combines multiple checks in one tool
  -Provides security scoring and prioritization
  -Saves time on manual analysis
  -Great for initial triage

## Limitations
  -May generate false positives
  -Requires setup (Docker recommended)
  -Dynamic analysis requires emulator setup
